The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, June 07, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE show				 																																	(State  Archaeological Museum, till June 15, 4 pm to 8 pm) A photography  exhibition of select views of the former capital of Bengal,  during the glory days of trade and commerce, now a site of  historical importance. Organised by the Directorate of Archaeology  and Museums, Government of West Bengal, and Centre for Archaeological  Studies and Training, Eastern India.  THE FILM				 																																	(Chitrabani,  June 7, 6 pm) A day in the life of an eight-year-old Santhal  tribal girl is the subject of this Bengali documentary film,  directed by Naren Banerjee of Shooters Paradise and produced  by Nandita Moitra.  THE BOOK				 																																	(Fareed  Zakaria) The book takes a look at liberty and democracy, the  concept and the reality, in the past and the future, and whether,  contrary to western belief, the two go hand in hand. The argument:  is democracy the ultimate solution to world problems, or the  root cause?  THE CD				 																																	(Americas  Greatest Hits) The eclectic country-rock trio of Dewey Bunnell,  Dan Peek and Gerry Beckley has enthralled an entire generation  with its magical music. This set comprises such delightful  numbers as Ventura Highway and Muskrat Love. 
